Substrate.notes: From transparent waters, with strong to moderate current with river beds formed by rocks, small stones and sand, scarce or absent aquatic vegetation (Ref. 40935).

Diet.notes: chiefly of algae, particularly diatoms and filamentous genera such as Spirogyra? alongside smaller amounts of invertebrates such as chironomids and bryozoans
Substrate.notes: under and among submerged rocks and boulders
Other.notes:
Temperature: 27 Ð 32 ¡C; this species will not thrive in cooler water.

pH: 6.0 Ð 8.0

Hardness: 54 Ð 268 ppm

Diet.notes: Mostly algivores, occationally feed on insect larvae
Other.notes:
*Diet, substrate, flow based on C. joropo. Male, upside down, guards an adhesive clutch of eggs by, more or less, covering it with his body; shallow (0.20Ð0.55 m) but well
oxygenated water (6.1Ð9.5 mg/L), and slightly basic pH (7.1Ð8.6); conductivity (10.4Ð258.0 _S) as well as
temperature (21Ð30¡C) are variable

Diet.notes: Algae is ''processed'' for the tiny microorganisms within and this is very hard to replicate in the aquarium.
